<div class="page">
  <h1>Workspace Templates</h1>

  <p>Several repositories serve as templates you can fork and customise for your own needs:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><a class="repo-link" href="/repos/claude-diary-planner-template/">Claude Diary Planner Template</a> &mdash; daily planning and journaling</li>
    <li><a class="repo-link" href="/repos/claude-budget-workspace-template/">Claude Budget Workspace Template</a> &mdash; personal finance management</li>
    <li><a class="repo-link" href="/repos/claude-communications-strategist-template/">Claude Communications Strategist Template</a> &mdash; media and comms workflows</li>
    <li><a class="repo-link" href="/repos/claude-writing-space-template/">Claude Writing Space Template</a> &mdash; long-form writing projects</li>
    <li><a class="repo-link" href="/repos/claude-home-assistant-manager-template/">Claude Home Assistant Manager Template</a> &mdash; smart home management</li>
    <li><a class="repo-link" href="/repos/claude-report-parsing-space-template/">Claude Report Parsing Space Template</a> &mdash; structured document analysis</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Each template comes with a <code>CLAUDE.md</code> file pre-written for that domain, slash commands tailored to common operations, and a directory structure that Claude knows how to work with.</p>

  <div style="margin-top: 2rem;">
    <a href="/?tag=Template" style="font-weight: 500;">Browse all templates in the index &rarr;</a>
  </div>
</div>

</BaseLayout>
